ian   Martini  , Polish surnames beginning with <i>Marcin-</i>, and Slovenian patronymics like <b>Martinčič</b> (see   Martincic  ). <i>Martin</i> is the most frequent surname in France and one of the most frequent surnames in Wallonia.","English: variant of   Marton  .","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Mártain</b>, ‘descendant of Martin’ (compare 1 above). Otherwise, a shortened form of   Gilmartin   or   McMartin  ; sometimes also spelled <i>Martyn</i>."]}]},{"name":"Gille","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Aegidus</i>, Old French <i>Gide</i>.  See  <b>Giles</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Críst","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Cristobál ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Dau Gille Críst of Mar was born about 1130, in Scotland as the daughter of Gilchrist 3rd Earl of Mar and Orabilis of Nes. She had at least 3 sons with Malcolm \"Máel Coluim\" de Lundie. She died in Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1130–":"umbes 1130–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1112–1171":"1112–1171","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1155–Male":"1155–Surnud","1170–1230":"1170–1230","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","–1203":"–1203","1203":"1203","1112":"1112","1100":"1100","1155":"1155","1230":"1230","1152":"1152","1130":"1130","about 1155":"umbes 1155","1171":"1171","about 1130":"umbes 1130","about 1152":"umbes 1152","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europe","Scotland?":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland","Lundin, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1130–":"noin 1130–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1112–1171":"1112–1171","1152–Male"